    "body": "<!--\r\n**Note:**\r\n- Did you search for similar issues already? Yes\r\n- Did you try the latest master branch or pre-release? Yes\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nI have a class defined in C/C++ header file, with tons of properties. \r\nThe problem is when I need that class in .pxd files, I have to re-define those\r\nproperties in .pxd files, and, there's not only 1 or 2 .pxd files, I have kinda \r\n10 .pxd files thus there are too much duplicated code in .pxd files.\r\n\r\nThis creates incomplete type:\r\n```cython\r\ncdef extern from \"myclass.hh\":\r\n    cppclass MyClass\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis creates a `dict` instead of a type with all properties\r\n(this works to include implementation file code .cc, .cpp but not headers):\r\n```cython\r\ncdef extern from \"myclass.hh:\r\n    cppclass MyClass:\r\n        pass\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nI wish that Cython as C/C++ parser and parse the C/C++ header files by itself\r\nso my .pxd files won't contain duplicated code again and again in different files.\r\nAlso when the C/C++ header file is changed, it is needed to change all those\r\n.pxd files that `cdef extern` from it.\r\n\r\nWith a C/C++ parser, and a new keyword for example `grab`, the whole\r\nheader file can be included into Cython with all things defined in that header file:\r\n```cython\r\ncdef extern from \"myclass.hh\":\r\n    cppclass MyClass:\r\n        grab\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\nI don't have any alternatives or work-arounds right now,\r\naccepting the duplicated code in .pxd files.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nNone.\r\n",
